<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98831165512289></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98831165512289><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/item.html?item=5734&mid=98831165512289>Tome of Ages</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 26th 3:00 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, as one of the (few) Cimmerii of Erollisi Marr, I saw this item drop.  The same wraith also had a Withered Leather Tunic, with very delectable statistics.<br><br>Archaon is indeed a Necromancer, and uses the Tome for his combat gear.  It has very decent statistics ignoring the charisma, and while it has been proven decisively that lower charisma has no positive effects, Archaon loves wallowing in filth :P  People get so caught up in powergaming, sheesh.  He can brag about having a single digit Charisma score with this equipped.  Don't remember if it's possible to go below zero, though I KNOW he has tried :)<br><br>As for the Tome of Ages, very interesting comments about this potentially having some use...  However my initial reaction is "not likely" since Miragul lived in a time period so dark it was said no history was taken down, as I recall.  The Book of Scale is similarly MAGIC/LORE, though...  but this seems more a grimoire, not a history.  The Hole was Old Paineel, the city Miragul founded, though he later ran off to pursue immortality in the north.  Just throwing out facts, worth digging around some more in that vein I suppose, though Verant's history with world events actually tying in to quests/real items is pretty shoddy.<br><br>B.M., Sometime Guardian of the Cimmerii, Erollisi Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
